FL,417,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1784823525
OL,3,CRansacked cafe owner says anti-social
OL,4,Cbehaviour ruining city centre
OL,6,F"We are dealing with addicts injecting
OL,7,Fin public spaces, including inside
OL,8,Fbusiness premises. We are dealing with
OL,9,Fattempted break-ins, vandalism, and
OL,10,Fnow full-scale burglaries where
OL,11,Findividuals, under the influence and
OL,12,Facting out of desperation, are
OL,13,Fsmashing their way into shops and
OL,14,Fcafes.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,417,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1784823525
OL,3,CRansacked cafe owner says anti-social
OL,4,Cbehaviour ruining city centre
OL,6,F"My own premises was recently targeted
OL,7,F` a keg thrown through the window, the
OL,8,Finterior destroyed when nothing of
OL,9,Fvalue could be taken. This is not an
OL,10,Fisolated event, it is part of a
OL,11,Fpattern that every business owner in
OL,12,Fthe area recognises.
OL,14,F"Mr Evans expressed concern at an
OL,15,Fincrease in rough sleeping, and
OL,16,F"individuals being left without
OL,17,Fsupport, intervention or a plan from
OL,18,Fthe authorities".
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AO]xD@AOUzD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,417,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1784823525
OL,3,CRansacked cafe owner says anti-social
OL,4,Cbehaviour ruining city centre
OL,6,F"The city centre has become a place
OL,7,Fwhere people are sleeping in doorways,
OL,8,Finjecting in alleyways and wandering
OL,9,Fthe streets in a state of distress.
OL,10,FThis is not only unsafe for businesses
OL,11,Fand the public, it is deeply inhumane
OL,12,Ffor those who are clearly in need of
OL,13,Fstructured help," he wrote.
OL,15,FMr Evans urged the council to take
OL,16,Faction, including a strategy to
OL,17,Faddress drug use, increased police and
OL,18,Fcommunity safety presence, a clear
OL,19,Fplan to support rough sleepers and
OL,20,Fengagement with business owners.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
